                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. Dept doubts feasibility Graham making informal interim report mid-Aug (last
                    para <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 114, Aug 1) because 1) his
                    obvious unwillingness devote himself to present crisis (Delhi tel 321 rptd Kar
                    21, Aug [<hi rend="italic">July</hi>] 23) 2) such report not essential to permit
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> action if necessary and 3) it wld
                    undoubtedly prejudice successful conclusion Graham present work by possibly
                    prematurely showing his hand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
